It&#8217;s understood the man attacked the child while he was playing in the street and stabbed him in the neck. JOHANNESBURG A 21-year-old man is due to appear in court on Wednesday morning in connection with the murder of a five-year-old boy in Orlando East, Soweto.It s understood the man attacked the child while he was playing in the street and stabbed him in the neck. The police s Phephi Matlou-Mthetho says the circumstances surrounding the murder are still unknown. A 21-year-old was arrested by the community and taken to Orlando Police Station where he s detained. 